.TH "gmap_pte_op_fixup" 9 "gmap_pte_op_fixup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gmap_pte_op_fixup \- force a page in and connect the gmap page table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gmap_pte_op_fixup
.BI "(struct gmap *gmap "  ","
.BI "unsigned long gaddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long vmaddr "  ","
.BI "int prot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gmap" 12
pointer to guest mapping meta data structure
.IP "gaddr" 12
virtual address in the guest address space
.IP "vmaddr" 12
address in the host process address space
.IP "prot" 12
indicates access rights: PROT_NONE, PROT_READ or PROT_WRITE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if the caller can retry __gmap_translate (might fail again),
-ENOMEM if out of memory and -EFAULT if anything goes wrong while fixing
up or connecting the gmap page table.
